data-triple-N3.o: "The Louvin Brothers were an American country music duo comprised of brothers Ira Lonnie Loudermilk (19241965) and Charlie Elzer Loudermilk (19272011) known as Ira and Charlie Louvin, respectively. The Brothers helped popularize close harmony, a genre of country music and are cousins to John D. Loudermilk, a Nashville Songwriters Hall of Fame member."@en
